Prerequisites
•	Visual Studio 2019 or 2022 (with ASP.NET workload)
•	SQL Server 2017+ or SQL Server Express
•	SQL Server Management Studio (SSMS) or Azure Data Studio
•	.NET Framework 4.8 Developer Pack

Step-by-Step Setup
1.	Clone the repository:  git clone https://github.com/your-org/ADMS_ERP.git
2.	Open ADMS_ERP.sln in Visual Studio
3.	Restore NuGet packages: right-click Solution > Restore NuGet Packages
4.	Run the SQL script: open ADMS_ERP_Database.sql in SSMS and execute (F5)
5.	Update Web.config connection string — change Data Source=. to your SQL Server name if needed
6.	Build the solution: Ctrl+Shift+B
7.	Press F5 to run. Browser opens at https://localhost:PORT/Account/Login
8.	Login with:  Email: admin@adms.com  |  Password: admin123

